00:00:48.450 --> 00:00:49.270 align:middle line:90%
Welcome, Judith.

00:00:49.270 --> 00:00:50.070 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh hi, Jeffrey.

00:00:50.070 --> 00:00:51.070 align:middle line:90%
It's great to be here.

00:00:51.070 --> 00:00:53.490 align:middle line:84%
>> It's a pleasure
to be with you again.

00:00:53.490 --> 00:00:55.530 align:middle line:90%
>> Same here.

00:00:55.530 --> 00:01:02.010 align:middle line:84%
>> You describe intuition as
an incredible source of wisdom.

00:01:02.010 --> 00:01:04.690 align:middle line:84%
And of course you're a
professional intuitive.

00:01:04.690 --> 00:01:05.580 align:middle line:90%
You've been trained.

00:01:05.580 --> 00:01:08.640 align:middle line:84%
You've worked in a university
setting in this regard.

00:01:08.640 --> 00:01:11.520 align:middle line:84%
But what you're saying is
that this source of wisdom

00:01:11.520 --> 00:01:13.100 align:middle line:90%
is available to everybody.

00:01:13.100 --> 00:01:13.900 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, it is.

00:01:13.900 --> 00:01:15.780 align:middle line:84%
And the reason I wrote
"Intuitive Healing" is

00:01:15.780 --> 00:01:17.730 align:middle line:84%
that people would come
up to me, and they say,

00:01:17.730 --> 00:01:19.410 align:middle line:90%
I have intuitions occasionally.

00:01:19.410 --> 00:01:21.750 align:middle line:84%
I'll have a deja vu, or my
gut feeling will tell me

00:01:21.750 --> 00:01:23.140 align:middle line:90%
this, that, or the other.

00:01:23.140 --> 00:01:25.720 align:middle line:84%
But it's not at my
fingertips every moment.

00:01:25.720 --> 00:01:27.780 align:middle line:84%
And as a psychiatrist
and intuitive,

00:01:27.780 --> 00:01:29.610 align:middle line:84%
I feel that it's so
important that we're

00:01:29.610 --> 00:01:31.980 align:middle line:84%
in touch with our
intuition moment to moment,

00:01:31.980 --> 00:01:33.030 align:middle line:90%
not just occasionally.

00:01:33.030 --> 00:01:35.160 align:middle line:84%
So it can inform
everything that we do.

00:01:35.160 --> 00:01:37.200 align:middle line:84%
It can inform how we
walk down the street,

00:01:37.200 --> 00:01:39.960 align:middle line:84%
how we can be present
in our body 100%

00:01:39.960 --> 00:01:42.270 align:middle line:84%
and tuning in and feeling
everything, as opposed

00:01:42.270 --> 00:01:44.850 align:middle line:84%
to just being in our minds
and worrying and thinking.

00:01:44.850 --> 00:01:47.640 align:middle line:84%
But being 100% in our body,
intuition will give us that.

00:01:47.640 --> 00:01:48.570 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:01:48.570 --> 00:01:51.960 align:middle line:84%
And in particular for
people who are actually ill,

00:01:51.960 --> 00:01:53.820 align:middle line:84%
which is often a
time when people

00:01:53.820 --> 00:01:57.460 align:middle line:84%
may feel that their intuition
really is failing them.

00:01:57.460 --> 00:01:58.260 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, yes.

00:01:58.260 --> 00:02:01.530 align:middle line:84%
Well, I suggest that people
practice their intuition

00:02:01.530 --> 00:02:03.930 align:middle line:84%
long before they could
get ill, if possible.

00:02:03.930 --> 00:02:05.490 align:middle line:90%
That's not always possible.

00:02:05.490 --> 00:02:07.450 align:middle line:84%
Because when you get in
touch with your body,

00:02:07.450 --> 00:02:09.120 align:middle line:84%
when you learn to
listen to its signals,

00:02:09.120 --> 00:02:12.240 align:middle line:84%
then when your body's
off, oftentimes intuition

00:02:12.240 --> 00:02:14.590 align:middle line:84%
can help you find
those subtler signals.

00:02:14.590 --> 00:02:16.740 align:middle line:84%
So when you do get
sick, then you really

00:02:16.740 --> 00:02:18.840 align:middle line:84%
know how to track your
body and help heal it.

00:02:18.840 --> 00:02:22.180 align:middle line:84%
>> One of the problems, I think,
is that when people become ill,

00:02:22.180 --> 00:02:25.960 align:middle line:84%
especially a serious illness,
that very strong emotions come

00:02:25.960 --> 00:02:26.760 align:middle line:90%
up.

00:02:26.760 --> 00:02:29.550 align:middle line:84%
They begin blaming
themselves for it.

00:02:29.550 --> 00:02:30.840 align:middle line:90%
>> It's so true.

00:02:30.840 --> 00:02:32.820 align:middle line:84%
And particularly in
the new age, there's

00:02:32.820 --> 00:02:35.950 align:middle line:84%
this idea that we create
our own illnesses.

00:02:35.950 --> 00:02:38.220 align:middle line:84%
And I really have a lot
of argument about that,

00:02:38.220 --> 00:02:40.200 align:middle line:84%
because who in their
right mind would ever

00:02:40.200 --> 00:02:41.670 align:middle line:90%
want to create an illness?

00:02:41.670 --> 00:02:44.400 align:middle line:84%
And I think if we
become ill, the premise

00:02:44.400 --> 00:02:46.770 align:middle line:84%
of intuitive feeling
is self compassion.

00:02:46.770 --> 00:02:49.560 align:middle line:84%
And it's looking at any
experience, including illness,

00:02:49.560 --> 00:02:51.510 align:middle line:84%
as a way to open
the heart, as a way

00:02:51.510 --> 00:02:53.970 align:middle line:84%
to learn about our bodies
and our intuitions,

00:02:53.970 --> 00:02:57.300 align:middle line:84%
rather than an opportunity
for self punishment.

00:02:57.300 --> 00:03:01.440 align:middle line:84%
>> And you have a series
of steps that you recommend

00:03:01.440 --> 00:03:02.910 align:middle line:90%
for people.

00:03:02.910 --> 00:03:05.970 align:middle line:84%
If they're confronting
any kind of a situation,

00:03:05.970 --> 00:03:08.550 align:middle line:84%
these are steps that
will help people to get

00:03:08.550 --> 00:03:10.470 align:middle line:90%
in touch with their intuitions.

00:03:10.470 --> 00:03:11.970 align:middle line:84%
>> Yes, in each
section of the book,

00:03:11.970 --> 00:03:15.000 align:middle line:84%
I go through five steps in every
single chapter because these

00:03:15.000 --> 00:03:17.700 align:middle line:84%
are the steps I use in
my psychiatric practice,

00:03:17.700 --> 00:03:20.730 align:middle line:84%
in my personal life,
and I teach my patients.

00:03:20.730 --> 00:03:22.910 align:middle line:84%
And I go through the steps
with everything I do.

00:03:22.910 --> 00:03:24.285 align:middle line:84%
When I wrote the
book, I thought,

00:03:24.285 --> 00:03:26.790 align:middle line:84%
what do I do that I can
teach everybody else?

00:03:26.790 --> 00:03:28.980 align:middle line:84%
Because we all can
learn intuition.

00:03:28.980 --> 00:03:30.870 align:middle line:84%
And I have developed
these five steps.

00:03:30.870 --> 00:03:34.260 align:middle line:84%
And briefly they are
noticing positive beliefs

00:03:34.260 --> 00:03:37.260 align:middle line:84%
about healing, which
is so important.

00:03:37.260 --> 00:03:41.040 align:middle line:84%
Developing beliefs that we could
connect with our innate healing

00:03:41.040 --> 00:03:43.590 align:middle line:84%
system and be a co-partner
in our own healing,

00:03:43.590 --> 00:03:44.860 align:middle line:90%
that's so important.

00:03:44.860 --> 00:03:48.390 align:middle line:84%
The second step is learning to
listen to the body's signals,

00:03:48.390 --> 00:03:50.190 align:middle line:84%
really getting in
touch with our bodies

00:03:50.190 --> 00:03:52.890 align:middle line:84%
so we can hear what's going
on, as opposed from living

00:03:52.890 --> 00:03:55.260 align:middle line:90%
from the neck up all the time.

00:03:55.260 --> 00:03:56.980 align:middle line:84%
And the third is
learning how to sense

00:03:56.980 --> 00:03:59.100 align:middle line:84%
subtle energies or
the energy field

00:03:59.100 --> 00:04:01.890 align:middle line:84%
around the body, which
can affect our health

00:04:01.890 --> 00:04:03.480 align:middle line:90%
and well-being.

00:04:03.480 --> 00:04:05.670 align:middle line:84%
And step four is learning
how to go in and ask

00:04:05.670 --> 00:04:06.720 align:middle line:90%
for inner guidance.

00:04:06.720 --> 00:04:08.625 align:middle line:84%
The sacred act of
closing your eyes,

00:04:08.625 --> 00:04:12.480 align:middle line:84%
of going inside, getting quiet,
and hearing that inner voice.

00:04:12.480 --> 00:04:13.780 align:middle line:90%
And we all have it.

00:04:13.780 --> 00:04:15.450 align:middle line:84%
Now I know I work
with people who feel

00:04:15.450 --> 00:04:16.742 align:middle line:90%
they don't have an inner voice.

00:04:16.742 --> 00:04:19.105 align:middle line:84%
A lot of attorneys or bank
presidents are very linear.

00:04:19.105 --> 00:04:21.480 align:middle line:84%
And they feel like when I tune
in, there's nothing there.

00:04:21.480 --> 00:04:22.313 align:middle line:90%
And that's not true.

00:04:22.313 --> 00:04:23.763 align:middle line:90%
We all have this.

00:04:23.763 --> 00:04:25.680 align:middle line:84%
And then the fifth step,
which is my favorite,

00:04:25.680 --> 00:04:28.060 align:middle line:84%
is learning to listen
to dreams, night dreams,

00:04:28.060 --> 00:04:30.300 align:middle line:84%
learning how to
remember and interpret

00:04:30.300 --> 00:04:33.630 align:middle line:84%
the incredible intuitions that
come through our night selves.

00:04:33.630 --> 00:04:36.990 align:middle line:84%
Every single night, we have
this great intuitive wellspring

00:04:36.990 --> 00:04:39.360 align:middle line:84%
that comes forth if we can
learn how to remember and tap

00:04:39.360 --> 00:04:40.650 align:middle line:90%
into it.

00:04:40.650 --> 00:04:44.580 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, it strikes me that it's
a good formula because if any

00:04:44.580 --> 00:04:46.350 align:middle line:84%
one of those methods
doesn't work,

00:04:46.350 --> 00:04:47.887 align:middle line:90%
one of the others is likely to.

00:04:47.887 --> 00:04:49.470 align:middle line:84%
>> You know, Jeffrey,
that's so right.

00:04:49.470 --> 00:04:51.887 align:middle line:84%
Because there's some times
when my intuition doesn't work,

00:04:51.887 --> 00:04:52.950 align:middle line:90%
I've seen.

00:04:52.950 --> 00:04:56.350 align:middle line:84%
If I'm very overly invested
in something, if I'm in love

00:04:56.350 --> 00:04:59.677 align:middle line:84%
and I can't read
somebody, sometimes my

00:04:59.677 --> 00:05:02.010 align:middle line:84%
going inside and asking for
inner guidance doesn't work.

00:05:02.010 --> 00:05:04.530 align:middle line:84%
But at those moments where
I'm too personally involved,

00:05:04.530 --> 00:05:06.060 align:middle line:90%
I turn to my dreams.

00:05:06.060 --> 00:05:08.880 align:middle line:84%
Because in the dream state,
there is no ego involved.

00:05:08.880 --> 00:05:11.340 align:middle line:84%
And so what I do and
what I teach people to do

00:05:11.340 --> 00:05:13.680 align:middle line:84%
is if you're stuck in
any aspect of your life,

00:05:13.680 --> 00:05:14.845 align:middle line:90%
to ask a question.

00:05:14.845 --> 00:05:16.470 align:middle line:84%
Let's say, how can
I improve my health?

00:05:16.470 --> 00:05:18.030 align:middle line:90%
Or how can I improve my energy?

00:05:18.030 --> 00:05:19.380 align:middle line:90%
And ask a dream.

00:05:19.380 --> 00:05:21.207 align:middle line:84%
And then the next
morning get very quiet

00:05:21.207 --> 00:05:23.040 align:middle line:84%
the first five minutes
you wake up, and then

00:05:23.040 --> 00:05:24.510 align:middle line:90%
write the dream down.

00:05:24.510 --> 00:05:27.270 align:middle line:84%
And then see how the answer
applies to the question.

00:05:27.270 --> 00:05:29.690 align:middle line:90%
And I lead my life this way.

00:05:29.690 --> 00:05:34.220 align:middle line:84%
>> You suggest that people
can use these techniques with

00:05:34.220 --> 00:05:36.020 align:middle line:90%
their own doctor, in fact.

00:05:36.020 --> 00:05:39.080 align:middle line:84%
>> With their own doctor,
absolutely, with themselves,

00:05:39.080 --> 00:05:41.570 align:middle line:84%
in any situation
they'll ever be in.

00:05:41.570 --> 00:05:44.330 align:middle line:84%
These are steps that
are internal steps.

00:05:44.330 --> 00:05:48.140 align:middle line:84%
You begin to activate them
and to become so familiar.

00:05:48.140 --> 00:05:51.320 align:middle line:84%
It's the kind of kinesthetic
to living life, learning

00:05:51.320 --> 00:05:53.210 align:middle line:84%
how to check in with
your body, sensing

00:05:53.210 --> 00:05:54.830 align:middle line:84%
how a person's
energy feels, seeing

00:05:54.830 --> 00:05:56.630 align:middle line:84%
if you're drained
by other people,

00:05:56.630 --> 00:05:58.760 align:middle line:84%
or seeing of another person
gives you energy, which

00:05:58.760 --> 00:06:00.560 align:middle line:90%
is a function of subtle energy.

00:06:00.560 --> 00:06:04.040 align:middle line:84%
And just noticing-- it's
like an artist's work.

00:06:04.040 --> 00:06:06.740 align:middle line:84%
Being an intuitive is
opening up to the artistry

00:06:06.740 --> 00:06:08.930 align:middle line:90%
and the sensibilities of life.

00:06:08.930 --> 00:06:11.190 align:middle line:84%
Being totally open is a very
passionate way of living.

00:06:11.190 --> 00:06:11.990 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:06:11.990 --> 00:06:14.090 align:middle line:90%
And sometimes it's interesting.

00:06:14.090 --> 00:06:17.030 align:middle line:84%
When we go to a doctor,
a doctor may be trained,

00:06:17.030 --> 00:06:18.680 align:middle line:84%
especially these
days when they want

00:06:18.680 --> 00:06:22.190 align:middle line:84%
to be open with their patients,
to say something to the effect

00:06:22.190 --> 00:06:24.133 align:middle line:84%
like, well, you have
a chronic condition.

00:06:24.133 --> 00:06:26.300 align:middle line:84%
You're going to have to
learn to live with this pain

00:06:26.300 --> 00:06:27.620 align:middle line:90%
the rest of your life.

00:06:27.620 --> 00:06:29.000 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, yeah.

00:06:29.000 --> 00:06:31.293 align:middle line:84%
Dr. Larry Dossey calls
this medical hexing.

00:06:31.293 --> 00:06:32.210 align:middle line:90%
And that's what it is.

00:06:32.210 --> 00:06:34.950 align:middle line:84%
You implant these negative
beliefs in people.

00:06:34.950 --> 00:06:37.250 align:middle line:84%
And we should never
listen to that.

00:06:37.250 --> 00:06:39.350 align:middle line:84%
We always need to
listen to what's inside

00:06:39.350 --> 00:06:40.970 align:middle line:84%
and always know
that we can heal.

00:06:40.970 --> 00:06:44.000 align:middle line:84%
In some shape or form, there's
always some option there.

00:06:44.000 --> 00:06:46.790 align:middle line:84%
I took intuitive healing
to the American Psychiatric

00:06:46.790 --> 00:06:50.210 align:middle line:84%
Association convention, which
is a convention of the most

00:06:50.210 --> 00:06:53.000 align:middle line:84%
traditional psychiatrists
in the country.

00:06:53.000 --> 00:06:54.500 align:middle line:84%
And I didn't know
what the response

00:06:54.500 --> 00:06:56.000 align:middle line:84%
would be because
sometimes doctors

00:06:56.000 --> 00:06:57.710 align:middle line:90%
can be a pretty rigid group.

00:06:57.710 --> 00:07:00.102 align:middle line:84%
And the people who attended
my workshop were so open,

00:07:00.102 --> 00:07:02.060 align:middle line:84%
and they were psychiatrists
from the heartland,

00:07:02.060 --> 00:07:03.470 align:middle line:84%
from the Midwest
who said, I want

00:07:03.470 --> 00:07:05.210 align:middle line:84%
to know how to use
these intuitive steps

00:07:05.210 --> 00:07:06.440 align:middle line:90%
with my patients.

00:07:06.440 --> 00:07:08.088 align:middle line:84%
And I went through
each step with them,

00:07:08.088 --> 00:07:10.130 align:middle line:84%
and they took it back,
and they wrote me letters,

00:07:10.130 --> 00:07:11.010 align:middle line:90%
and they use it.

00:07:11.010 --> 00:07:12.740 align:middle line:84%
And this just makes
my heart sing.

00:07:12.740 --> 00:07:15.110 align:middle line:84%
Because my passion
is to change the face

00:07:15.110 --> 00:07:17.960 align:middle line:84%
of traditional medicine to
bring back this sense of heart,

00:07:17.960 --> 00:07:21.350 align:middle line:84%
to bring back this sense of
deep intuition in the doctor,

00:07:21.350 --> 00:07:23.670 align:middle line:90%
as well as the patient.

00:07:23.670 --> 00:07:26.000 align:middle line:84%
It's not just about a
doctor being intuitive.

00:07:26.000 --> 00:07:28.490 align:middle line:84%
I help all my patients
to get in touch

00:07:28.490 --> 00:07:31.370 align:middle line:84%
with this sense of inner
self because then they

00:07:31.370 --> 00:07:34.677 align:middle line:84%
can leave therapy and have
something very real inside

00:07:34.677 --> 00:07:37.010 align:middle line:84%
of themselves they can turn
to through the ups and downs

00:07:37.010 --> 00:07:38.180 align:middle line:90%
of life.

00:07:38.180 --> 00:07:41.920 align:middle line:84%
>> Now I had, in my own
practice as a psychologist,

00:07:41.920 --> 00:07:46.490 align:middle line:84%
an interesting case, a patient
who was really very intuitive.

00:07:46.490 --> 00:07:49.640 align:middle line:84%
But she kept insisting,
against all of my protests,

00:07:49.640 --> 00:07:52.130 align:middle line:84%
that she did have to
come to accept that she

00:07:52.130 --> 00:07:53.780 align:middle line:90%
had a chronic condition.

00:07:53.780 --> 00:07:57.320 align:middle line:84%
It was MS. And she felt that
all of the effort of people

00:07:57.320 --> 00:07:59.270 align:middle line:84%
to think that you
can heal yourself

00:07:59.270 --> 00:08:01.400 align:middle line:84%
was getting in the
way of her coming

00:08:01.400 --> 00:08:03.350 align:middle line:90%
to terms with her illness.

00:08:03.350 --> 00:08:05.080 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, she would
know best then.

00:08:05.080 --> 00:08:06.860 align:middle line:84%
I always honor what
my patients say.

00:08:06.860 --> 00:08:09.050 align:middle line:84%
If that's what they feel,
then you go with it.

00:08:09.050 --> 00:08:10.940 align:middle line:90%
You help them in their own path.

00:08:10.940 --> 00:08:14.340 align:middle line:84%
I never try and project what
I believe is best for them

00:08:14.340 --> 00:08:15.140 align:middle line:90%
onto someone.

00:08:15.140 --> 00:08:18.200 align:middle line:84%
Always intuitive healing is
about listening to the person

00:08:18.200 --> 00:08:20.480 align:middle line:84%
and going with what
they believe in.

00:08:20.480 --> 00:08:22.640 align:middle line:84%
But healing comes in
all shapes and forms.

00:08:22.640 --> 00:08:24.980 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes the body does
not heal completely

00:08:24.980 --> 00:08:27.260 align:middle line:84%
of chronic pain or
chronic illness.

00:08:27.260 --> 00:08:29.000 align:middle line:90%
And yet the heart opens.

00:08:29.000 --> 00:08:31.340 align:middle line:84%
And so what is the
ultimate healing?

00:08:31.340 --> 00:08:34.549 align:middle line:84%
You always have to look at
illness as an opportunity

00:08:34.549 --> 00:08:37.490 align:middle line:84%
to open the heart, or anything
that we go through in the ups

00:08:37.490 --> 00:08:38.659 align:middle line:90%
and downs of life.

00:08:38.659 --> 00:08:40.350 align:middle line:84%
When I was writing
"Intuitive Healing,"

00:08:40.350 --> 00:08:42.080 align:middle line:90%
I had a very clear premise.

00:08:42.080 --> 00:08:44.660 align:middle line:84%
And that was that love is
the most powerful healing

00:08:44.660 --> 00:08:48.050 align:middle line:84%
force in the universe, and
