>> They did.

00:17:34.790 --> 00:17:38.065 align:middle line:84%
I grew up a very intuitive
child in Beverly Hills.

00:17:38.065 --> 00:17:39.565 align:middle line:84%
And both my parents
were physicians.

00:17:39.565 --> 00:17:41.993 align:middle line:84%
I have 25 physicians
in my family.

00:17:41.993 --> 00:17:44.410 align:middle line:84%
And here I was this little
girl that could pick things up.

00:17:44.410 --> 00:17:47.560 align:middle line:84%
I could pick up deaths and
illnesses and earthquakes.

00:17:47.560 --> 00:17:49.900 align:middle line:84%
And finally my parents
got so exasperated,

00:17:49.900 --> 00:17:52.240 align:middle line:84%
they just said, never mention
anything else in our home

00:17:52.240 --> 00:17:53.320 align:middle line:90%
again about this.

00:17:53.320 --> 00:17:55.720 align:middle line:84%
So I grew up believing there
was something wrong with me

00:17:55.720 --> 00:17:58.940 align:middle line:84%
that I was able to sense
and know about these things.

00:17:58.940 --> 00:18:01.120 align:middle line:84%
And so my healing
journey has been

00:18:01.120 --> 00:18:03.700 align:middle line:84%
coming to terms with
this intuitive self

00:18:03.700 --> 00:18:07.690 align:middle line:84%
and making it a part of my work
as a psychiatrist, as a human

00:18:07.690 --> 00:18:10.710 align:middle line:84%
being, as a woman, not
splitting off parts of myself,

00:18:10.710 --> 00:18:12.780 align:middle line:84%
but being everything
all at once.

00:18:12.780 --> 00:18:15.610 align:middle line:84%
And I feel that this is so
important because in my past,

00:18:15.610 --> 00:18:18.670 align:middle line:84%
I never felt safe to
express my intuitions.

00:18:18.670 --> 00:18:20.890 align:middle line:90%
And now it's my passion.

00:18:20.890 --> 00:18:23.110 align:middle line:84%
Having found my voice
is the greatest gift

00:18:23.110 --> 00:18:24.340 align:middle line:90%
I've ever been given.

00:18:24.340 --> 00:18:27.340 align:middle line:84%
>> You describe sometimes
the necessity to listen

00:18:27.340 --> 00:18:31.090 align:middle line:84%
to an intuition, even when
it goes against what we may

00:18:31.090 --> 00:18:33.730 align:middle line:90%
logically think is correct.

00:18:33.730 --> 00:18:36.280 align:middle line:84%
For example, at one
time in your career,

00:18:36.280 --> 00:18:38.860 align:middle line:84%
you got the intuition
that you were

00:18:38.860 --> 00:18:42.280 align:middle line:84%
going to pursue the path
of being a medical doctor,

00:18:42.280 --> 00:18:44.710 align:middle line:84%
even though you had spent
much of your life rebelling

00:18:44.710 --> 00:18:48.090 align:middle line:84%
against that very
aspect of your family.

00:18:48.090 --> 00:18:48.910 align:middle line:90%
>> It's true.

00:18:48.910 --> 00:18:50.980 align:middle line:84%
When I was 20, I was
living with my boyfriend

00:18:50.980 --> 00:18:53.710 align:middle line:84%
in Venice Beach in this old
converted brick laundromat.

00:18:53.710 --> 00:18:56.410 align:middle line:84%
And I was working in the towel
department in the maid company.

00:18:56.410 --> 00:18:58.870 align:middle line:84%
And I was working in a
parapsychology lab at that time

00:18:58.870 --> 00:19:00.530 align:middle line:90%
at UCLA also as a volunteer.

00:19:00.530 --> 00:19:02.920 align:middle line:84%
And I had this dream that
came to me that told me

00:19:02.920 --> 00:19:05.590 align:middle line:84%
I was going to get an MD
to become a psychiatrist

00:19:05.590 --> 00:19:08.140 align:middle line:84%
to help legitimize
intuition in medicine.

00:19:08.140 --> 00:19:11.620 align:middle line:84%
And this was at a time when
I had no desire whatsoever

00:19:11.620 --> 00:19:12.640 align:middle line:90%
to go into medicine.

00:19:12.640 --> 00:19:15.220 align:middle line:84%
But because I was beginning
to honor this intuitive

00:19:15.220 --> 00:19:18.340 align:middle line:84%
part of myself, I enrolled in
one course in a junior college

00:19:18.340 --> 00:19:19.930 align:middle line:90%
just to see how it would go.

00:19:19.930 --> 00:19:23.750 align:middle line:84%
And one became two became 14
years of medical training.

00:19:23.750 --> 00:19:27.155 align:middle line:84%
And so I had an intuitive dream
that signaled my true calling.

00:19:27.155 --> 00:19:29.025 align:middle line:90%
And thank god I listened.

00:19:29.025 --> 00:19:31.150 align:middle line:84%
Because many of my patients
and many people I know,

00:19:31.150 --> 00:19:32.680 align:middle line:90%
you get these kind of dreams.

00:19:32.680 --> 00:19:34.870 align:middle line:84%
And it's so impractical,
or the rational mind

00:19:34.870 --> 00:19:37.000 align:middle line:84%
doesn't understand it,
so you don't do it.

00:19:37.000 --> 00:19:38.560 align:middle line:90%
And you miss out on so much.

00:19:38.560 --> 00:19:40.750 align:middle line:84%
And part of the message
of intuitive healing

00:19:40.750 --> 00:19:42.010 align:middle line:90%
is listen to these dreams.

00:19:42.010 --> 00:19:45.070 align:middle line:84%
Listen to these intuitions
that are signaling a closer

00:19:45.070 --> 00:19:47.260 align:middle line:84%
relationship with
your truer self.

00:19:47.260 --> 00:19:50.590 align:middle line:84%
Have the guts to act on it, and
miraculous things will happen.

00:19:50.590 --> 00:19:54.340 align:middle line:84%
>> Because oftentimes it seems
as if illness results when we

00:19:54.340 --> 00:19:55.850 align:middle line:90%
don't listen to our intuitions.

00:19:55.850 --> 00:19:56.650 align:middle line:90%
>> It's true.

00:19:56.650 --> 00:19:57.755 align:middle line:90%
Our body rebels.

00:19:57.755 --> 00:19:59.380 align:middle line:84%
If we do something
that's off, it we'll

00:19:59.380 --> 00:20:01.420 align:middle line:90%
keep turning up the volume.

00:20:01.420 --> 00:20:03.780 align:middle line:84%
One intuition that we
have is exhaustion.

00:20:03.780 --> 00:20:06.770 align:middle line:84%
That's our body's signal
that's telling us, slow down.

00:20:06.770 --> 00:20:08.530 align:middle line:84%
And if we don't, then
we'll get symptoms.

00:20:08.530 --> 00:20:10.322 align:middle line:84%
If we don't, then we'll
get larger symptoms

00:20:10.322 --> 00:20:11.445 align:middle line:90%
and larger symptoms.

00:20:11.445 --> 00:20:13.570 align:middle line:84%
And it's not that our body
is trying to torment us.

00:20:13.570 --> 00:20:15.190 align:middle line:90%
It's trying to wake us up.

00:20:15.190 --> 00:20:19.480 align:middle line:84%
But our minds are so
persistently counterintuitive

00:20:19.480 --> 00:20:22.390 align:middle line:84%
that intuitive
healing means coming

00:20:22.390 --> 00:20:26.380 align:middle line:84%
to grips with what the body says
and honoring it and changing

00:20:26.380 --> 00:20:27.340 align:middle line:90%
our life accordingly.

00:20:27.340 --> 00:20:32.470 align:middle line:84%
And then the sense of joy and
commitment and joy of living

00:20:32.470 --> 00:20:33.700 align:middle line:90%
will come back.

00:20:33.700 --> 00:20:36.730 align:middle line:84%
>> You tell a wonderful story
in your book about being

00:20:36.730 --> 00:20:40.250 align:middle line:84%
in a woman's prison,
working with women,

00:20:40.250 --> 00:20:43.000 align:middle line:84%
people who we might think
are beyond redemption

00:20:43.000 --> 00:20:44.350 align:middle line:90%
because they're criminals.

00:20:44.350 --> 00:20:45.950 align:middle line:90%
And you point out that even--

00:20:45.950 --> 00:20:46.750 align:middle line:90%
>> That's the mind.

00:20:46.750 --> 00:20:50.080 align:middle line:84%
>> --even in those situations,
the intuition can be a very

00:20:50.080 --> 00:20:51.670 align:middle line:90%
vibrant, vital force.

00:20:51.670 --> 00:20:52.470 align:middle line:90%
>> Huge.

00:20:52.470 --> 00:20:55.690 align:middle line:84%
I spoke at this women's prison
in Danbury, Connecticut.

00:20:55.690 --> 00:20:57.510 align:middle line:90%
150 women came.

00:20:57.510 --> 00:21:00.000 align:middle line:84%
Took their free time off,
which is a big thing,

00:21:00.000 --> 00:21:01.770 align:middle line:90%
to come to this workshop.

00:21:01.770 --> 00:21:04.650 align:middle line:84%
And I said to them, how many of
you listen to your intuition?

00:21:04.650 --> 00:21:06.975 align:middle line:84%
How many of you knew that
something was off when

00:21:06.975 --> 00:21:08.100 align:middle line:90%
you committed these crimes?

00:21:08.100 --> 00:21:10.440 align:middle line:84%
And nearly the whole
room raised their hand.

00:21:10.440 --> 00:21:12.390 align:middle line:84%
And I said, well, why
didn't you listen?

00:21:12.390 --> 00:21:15.610 align:middle line:84%
And they said, well, we just
wanted to go ahead with it.

00:21:15.610 --> 00:21:16.410 align:middle line:90%
We didn't listen.

00:21:16.410 --> 00:21:18.285 align:middle line:84%
We didn't believe in
our intuition, whatever.

00:21:18.285 --> 00:21:19.470 align:middle line:90%
And we ended up here.

00:21:19.470 --> 00:21:21.810 align:middle line:84%
And now the whole group
went into meditation,

00:21:21.810 --> 00:21:25.230 align:middle line:84%
150 people in this prison,
with the prison yard

00:21:25.230 --> 00:21:27.988 align:middle line:84%
outside blaring with
the voices coming

00:21:27.988 --> 00:21:29.030 align:middle line:90%
through the loudspeakers.

00:21:29.030 --> 00:21:30.990 align:middle line:84%
And there are 150
women meditating,

00:21:30.990 --> 00:21:32.970 align:middle line:90%
doing intuitive healing.

00:21:32.970 --> 00:21:35.040 align:middle line:84%
And long ago, I've
given up any kind

00:21:35.040 --> 00:21:37.070 align:middle line:90%
of stereotype of who does this.

00:21:37.070 --> 00:21:38.750 align:middle line:90%
Now this is a human endeavor.

00:21:38.750 --> 00:21:41.110 align:middle line:84%
If anyone is interested
in intuitive healing,

00:21:41.110 --> 00:21:43.770 align:middle line:84%
it can open up just
a beautiful garden

00:21:43.770 --> 00:21:48.000 align:middle line:84%
inside that just keeps getting
larger and larger and larger.

00:21:48.000 --> 00:21:49.200 align:middle line:90%
There's no end to it.

00:21:49.200 --> 00:21:52.080 align:middle line:84%
I consider myself a perpetual
student of intuition.

00:21:52.080 --> 00:21:54.150 align:middle line:84%
>> No matter how many
times, in other words,

00:21:54.150 --> 00:21:57.045 align:middle line:84%
that we have failed to
listen to our intuitions,

00:21:57.045 --> 00:21:59.620 align:middle line:90%
we can always turn that around.

00:21:59.620 --> 00:22:00.420 align:middle line:90%
>> Always.

00:22:00.420 --> 00:22:01.980 align:middle line:84%
I didn't listen
for so long, but I

00:22:01.980 --> 00:22:05.830 align:middle line:84%
learned by when I didn't listen,
only bad things happened.

00:22:05.830 --> 00:22:08.080 align:middle line:84%
And when I did listen, only
wonderful things happened,

00:22:08.080 --> 00:22:10.560 align:middle line:84%
but I had to go through a
period of that battering of not

00:22:10.560 --> 00:22:11.370 align:middle line:90%
listening.

00:22:11.370 --> 00:22:13.980 align:middle line:84%
The willfulness that says,
no, but I want it to happen.

00:22:13.980 --> 00:22:15.480 align:middle line:84%
My intuition is
saying, no, but it's

00:22:15.480 --> 00:22:16.730 align:middle line:90%
not going to happen right now.

00:22:16.730 --> 00:22:17.530 align:middle line:90%
Just relax.

00:22:17.530 --> 00:22:18.905 align:middle line:84%
No, I'm going to
push through it.

00:22:18.905 --> 00:22:19.740 align:middle line:90%
That's the mind.

00:22:19.740 --> 00:22:21.782 align:middle line:84%
So you have to go through
those kind of struggles

00:22:21.782 --> 00:22:24.840 align:middle line:84%
to realize if you listen,
wonderful things always happen.

00:22:24.840 --> 00:22:26.700 align:middle line:84%
But it's human to go
through the struggle.

00:22:26.700 --> 00:22:28.290 align:middle line:90%
>> The struggle does seem human.

00:22:28.290 --> 00:22:29.630 align:middle line:90%
I know I go through it.

00:22:29.630 --> 00:22:30.430 align:middle line:90%
>> Of course.

00:22:30.430 --> 00:22:34.140 align:middle line:84%
>> But you suggest that
everybody can reach a point

00:22:34.140 --> 00:22:37.420 align:middle line:84%
where we can feel very confident
of all of our decisions.

00:22:37.420 --> 00:22:38.220 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, yes.

00:22:38.220 --> 00:22:39.180 align:middle line:90%
Oh, yes.

00:22:39.180 --> 00:22:40.950 align:middle line:84%
But sometimes you
don't feel confident.

00:22:40.950 --> 00:22:42.780 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes the fear
is going, I'm afraid.

00:22:42.780 --> 00:22:43.580 align:middle line:90%
I'm afraid.

00:22:43.580 --> 00:22:45.580 align:middle line:84%
But your intuition is
saying, yes, go ahead.

00:22:45.580 --> 00:22:46.380 align:middle line:90%
It's a choice.

00:22:46.380 --> 00:22:49.010 align:middle line:84%
You have to decide what
you want to listen to.

00:22:49.010 --> 00:22:51.970 align:middle line:84%
And the great thing is if you
listen to your intuition enough

00:22:51.970 --> 00:22:54.840 align:middle line:84%
and it affirms you enough, at
that moment when you're unsure,

00:22:54.840 --> 00:22:56.090 align:middle line:90%
you'll go with your intuition.

00:22:56.090 --> 00:22:59.070 align:middle line:84%
>> Judith Orloff, thank you
so much for being with me.

00:22:59.070 --> 00:22:59.970 align:middle line:90%
It's been a joy.

00:22:59.970 --> 00:23:02.490 align:middle line:84%
>> Oh, it was a joy
for me too, Jeffrey.

00:23:02.490 --> 00:23:06.210 align:middle line:84%
>> And thank you
for being with us.

